TEXT 976 -336 Left 2 ;The following parameters can be defined by right-clicking on the LT7170 symbol.\n \nFrequency_switch -- in Hz, sets switching frequency\n \nVout_range -- sets maximum output range, 0 for 1.375V, 1 for 2.75V, 2 for 5.5V\n \nVout_command -- in volt, sets output voltage\n \nTon_delay & Ton_rise -- in sec, set ON delay and soft-start time\nToff_delay & Toff_fall -- in sec, set OFF delay and soft-off time \n \nIlim_range -- sets current limit options:\n     0 positive valley current limit of 9A per phase, negative valley current limit of -6A\n   1 positive valley current limit of 13A per phase, negative valley current limit of -7.6A\n   2 positive valley current limit of 15.6A per phase, negative valley current limit of -9.4A\n   3 positive valley current limit of 21.4A per phase, negative valley current limit of -12A \n \nGMEA_control--Sets Error Amp parameters, N=0 to 31\nGmEA = 0.15mS*(n+1)/(2^VOUT_RANGE)    (relative to VSENSE inputs)\n ImaxOutEA = 8.5uA*(n+1) \n \nRITH--in ohm, programmable internal compensation\n \nCITH--in Farad, programmable internal compensation\nMFR_PWM_PHASE-- in degree, sets the master phase delay in 15-degree increments with respect to the SYNC frequency if present.\nVout_UV_Fault_Limit and Vout_OV_Fault_Limit --- in volt, set the undervoltage and overvoltage fault limit for the Pgood output\nVout_UV_Warn_Limit and Vout_OV_Warn_Limit-- in volt, set the undervoltage and overvoltage warning limit for the Alert output\nMFR_PWM_THRSHOLD, Output voltage threshold to determine that the output has decayed sufficiently to reenable the channel
